[84.535443, "o", "\u001b[90m# ── ask the bot ──\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[85.062591, "o", "\u001b[32m$\u001b[0m \u001b[36m.venv/bin/python rag.py ask \"What is a backward-compatible API change?\"\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[90.26971, "o", "A backward-compatible API change is a modification that does not break existing integrations or code relying on the API. Stripe considers the following changes to be backward-compatible:\r\n\r\n- Adding new API resources.\r\n- Adding new optional request parameters to existing API methods.\r\n- Adding new properties to existing API responses.\r\n- Changing the order of properties in existing API responses.\r\n- Changing the length or format of opaque strings, such as object IDs and error messages.\r\n- Adding new event types.\r\n- Ensuring webhooks gracefully handle unfamiliar event types.\r\n\r\nThese types of changes allow developers to upgrade their applications without requiring modifications to existing code. [Source](https://stripe.com/docs/upgrades)\r\n"]
[92.37243, "o", "\r\n"]
[92.372514, "o", "\u001b[1mcrawl\u001b[0m \u001b[90m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1mdiff\u001b[0m \u001b[90m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1membed deltas only\u001b[0m \u001b[90m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1mfresh answer\u001b[0m\r\n"]
